        "content": "<p>Is it impossible by design that you cannot modify data within a <code>Pin&lt;KBox&lt;T&gt;&gt;</code>, even if a field in <code>T</code> is not marked with the pin marker?</p>\n<p>My understanding so far has been that Pin is just about making things unmovable in memory, not immutable per se.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#[pin_data]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Job</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">credits</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"cp\">#[pin]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">T</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">done_fence</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Option</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">ARef</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">DmaFence</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">i32</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">hardware_fence</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Option</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">ARef</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">DmaFence</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">i32</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">nr_of_deps</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">//    dependencies: List, // TODO implement dependency list</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">submit_job</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">U</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">job</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Pin</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">KBox</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Job</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">U</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">ARef</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">DmaFence</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">i32</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">job_cost</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">job</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">credits</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// TODO: It would be nice if the done_fence's seqno actually matches the</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// submission order. To do that, however, we'd need to protect job</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// creation with InnerJobqueue's spinlock. Is that worth it?</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">//let enq = EnqueuedJob::new(job, &amp;self.fctx)?;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">done_fence</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">fctx</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_arc_borrow</span><span class=\"p\">().</span><span class=\"n\">new_fence</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">42</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">i32</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">// Get the fence for the user.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">job</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">done_fence</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Some</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">done_fence</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">clone</span><span class=\"p\">());</span>\n\n\n\n<span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">E0594</span><span class=\"p\">]:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">cannot</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">assign</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dereference</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">core</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">pin</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Pin</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">kbox</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Job</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">U</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Kmalloc</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">drm</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">jq</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">277</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">9</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">277</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">         </span><span class=\"n\">job</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">done_fence</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Some</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">done_fence</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">clone</span><span class=\"p\">());</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">         </span><span class=\"o\">^^^^^^^^^^^^^^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cannot</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">assign</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">help</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">trait</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">DerefMut</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">required</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">modify</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">through</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dereference</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">but</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">it</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">implemented</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">core</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">pin</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Pin</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">kbox</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Job</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">U</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Kmalloc</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 561658367,
