    {
        "content": "<p>You can use projections to do that.</p>",
        "id": 561659148,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1764770523
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">job</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">project</span><span class=\"p\">().</span><span class=\"n\">done_fence</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Some</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">done_fence</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">clone</span><span class=\"p\">());</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 561659226,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1764770544
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Possibly you need <code>job.as_mut().project()</code></p>",
        "id": 561659248,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1764770549
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>See commit 619db96daf942dad974c6c8157ed06d52f7bb969. It uses the feature in <code>rust/kernel/workqueue.rs</code></p>",
        "id": 561659659,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1764770659
    },
    {
